  "prompt": "How much does an IAS earn in hand for services?",
  "response": "The salary of an Indian Administrative Service (IAS) officer varies based on their pay level and years of service. Here's a general breakdown:\n\n1. Entry-level salary (Basic Pay):\n- Approximately \u20b956,100 per month at the start of their career\n\n2. Total In-Hand Salary:\n- At entry level: Around \u20b970,000-\u20b980,000 per month\n- After a few years of service: Can go up to \u20b91-1.5 lakhs per month\n\n3. Additional Benefits:\n- House rent allowance\n- Travel allowance\n- Medical benefits\n- Retirement benefits\n- Free official accommodation\n- Domestic and international travel opportunities\n\n4. Salary Growth:\n- Increases with promotions and years of service\n- At senior levels, can reach up to \u20b92-3 lakhs per month\n\n5. Other Perks:\n- Prestigious government position\n- Career growth opportunities\n- Power and influence in administrative roles\n\nNote: These figures are approximate and can vary slightly based on specific postings, location, and current government pay scales.\n\nThe exact salary can be confirmed from the latest government pay commission guidelines.",
